{"title":"What should I ask Alan Taylor?","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/882090581/0/marginalrevolution~What-should-I-ask-Alan-Taylor.html","date":1713685757000,"content":"<p>He is one of the greatest of living American historians, here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Taylor_(historian)\" target=\"_blank\">from Wikipedia</a>:</p>\r\n<blockquote><p><b>Alan Shaw Taylor</b> (born June 17, 1955) is an American historian and scholar who is the Thomas Jefferson Memorial Foundation Professor of History at the <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Virginia\">University of Virginia</a>.<sup></sup> A specialist in the early history of the United States, Taylor has written extensively about the <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colonial_history_of_the_United_States\">colonial history of the United States</a>, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_American_Revolution\">the American Revolution</a> and the <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_United_States_(1789%E2%80%931849)\">early American Republic</a>. Taylor has received two <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulitzer_Prizes\">Pulitzer Prizes</a> and the <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bancroft_Prize\">Bancroft Prize</a>, and was also a finalist for the <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Book_Award\">National Book Award</a> for non-fiction.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>He has a new and excellent book out, namely <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/American-Civil-Wars-Continental-1850-1873/dp/1324035285/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2571AMZ60QZKV&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.bGQTb_DhxmV6eGfbe16DeZwshnoP50yOHnC_0oikgXCNRMez071w3HgPmbmNAp7VbBy-dhLvTuFXzP1xagTlnTgexW9lQW-joN_4zTXVPWpE_UCv9ffeQhGNLWjWh_rk6-kPEnRHNB32a51YEnaFyD9rb6A22jmfIDh5VQ_xlNwyyOj3WnRX06HK-71VWgUv2rKsBNOBg-1QjXvhJptpzY4K3qfLwUyoi2epwUOrMeM.0Scl3w7rotxmR6zBPXZjMyMTfwyhB8-SH5M4bDYE5IA&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=alan+taylor+american+civil+wars&amp;qid=1713635303&amp;sprefix=alan+taylor+american+civil+wars%2Caps%2C71&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">American Civil Wars: A Continental History 1850-1873</a>.  Among his other virtues, he is renowned for tying in American history to developments in Canada, Mexico, and the Caribbean.  So what should I ask him?</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/04/what-should-i-ask-alan-taylor.html\">What should I ask Alan Taylor?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/882090581/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/882090581/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/882090581/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/882090581/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/882090581/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/882090581/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a hre